Description of the RBCS and RBS composite sensors
Redundancy Bus - Manuel utilisateur - vPlus.En1 - P04
A FrSky radio with firmware can handle up to 32 sensors. If the information contained in RBCS and RBS
had been directly available as native sensors, the alone would use 33 sensors!
However, it remains possible to obtain one or more information from RBCS and RBS through the use of an LUA script as described
Imagine that the internal value of RBS is 1227 (this value is recoverable only with an LUA script).
This decimal value 1227 can also be written in binary by a succession of 1 and 0 called "Bit".
Each of the "bits" that make up the value of RBS represents an information that can only take two states:
